[SN]TITLE[SN]
Anglesey 'sex addict' jailed for historic child abuse

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A 69-year-old man who sexually abused a girl and boy over a period of several years has been jailed for 13 years.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Robert Parry of Trefor, Anglesey, admitted 18 charges of abuse, including the attempted rape of the girl when she was 12-years-old.
Parry was placed on the sex offenders' register for life following the hearing at Caernarfon Crown Court on Wednesday.
Sentencing the 69-year-old, Judge Huw Rees said: "You effectively robbed them of their childhood."
The court heard how Parry told police he was as a sex addict and in need of help.
Elen Owen. prosecuting, said: "He said he didn't get gratification but a buzz."
Dafydd Roberts, defending, said Parry wished to make a public apology for his "reprehensible behaviour."
